1. He was named canon of Rheims Cathedral when he was 16
2. He is considered the founder of the first Catholic schools
3. The De La Salle Brothers were the first Roman Catholic religious teaching order that did not include any priests.
4. He was a pedagogical thinker
5. He was canonize by Pope Leo XIII on May 24, 1990
6. He was proclaimed as the Patron Saint of Teachers
7. He  became involved in education little by little, without ever consciously setting out to do so
8. He established a school for poor to help Adrian Nyel
9. His work quickly spread through France and, after his death, continued to spread across the globe
10. He died on Good Friday
